The paper deals with the theoretical model of self-assembly via co-transcriptional folding, which involves computational geometry, graph theory, and combinatorics. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the folding of shapes, which involves simulation and optimization, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper explores the influence of delay, which involves game theory and decision-making, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a possible sub-category.
